
[1]paragraph

   PAR'AGRAPH, n. [Gr. a marginal note; to write near or beyond the text;
   beyond, and to write.] A distinct part of a discourse or writing; any
   portion or section of a writing or chapter which relates to a
   particular point, whether consisting of one sentence or many sentences.
   A paragraph is sometimes marked, but more generally, a paragraph is
   distinguished only by a break in the composition or lines.

   PAR'AGRAPH, v.t. To form or write paragraphs.
